<br>
The glazed, scared, and confused look in her beautiful dark eyes made him pause and his words caught in his throat. He loved this woman, would always love her, and if things were different, he would have spent the rest of his life with her. But men make mistakes, and he made a mistake, and it was his duty---no, his father's words came to mind now---his *privilege* to father Myrielle Ironforge's child. Not only was marrying the girl Tobias's duty, but it would herald the profitable joining of two forges, securing trade in both the east and west of Antonica. There was no way around it; his duty to his father was clear. Perhaps he and Fajera could still love one another, it wasn't unheard of for prosperous men to keep a mistress. And Fajera really wouldn't be his mistress, but his true love. The marriage to Myrielle was really just business, anyway---he just unwittingly brokered the deal the night he took her to his bed in Qeynos. Even that Fajera might understand. They were very open and frank about discussing such things. <br>
<br>
But no, Fajera would never be a mistress. He knew that even before his thoughts grasped at the hope. And he wouldn't want that for her. She deserved someone devoted to her, as he was, but who could also be her lifemate, companion, husband. <br>
<br>
He reached for her, how could he not? The tears ran freely down his cheeks as he pressed his lips to hers, felt the tremble in her shoulders. &quot;Oh my love, I'm so sorry. So sorry. Please forgive me. Oh gods, forgive me,&quot; he whispered brokenly as she melted into his arms. <br>
<br>
&quot;Shhh,&quot; he heard her say. &quot;Shhh, my sweet Lover. Whatever it is can't be so bad. We'll work through it. Talk to me, Lover, talk to me.&quot;<br>
<br>
The fear was gone from her face as he pulled away, and the hope shining there was even more terrible to him than the anxiety. He realized that she truly had no idea how bad it could be. That she was so confident in the commitment of their love that she couldn't foresee what he was about to say. <br>
<br>
Steeling his nerves, he wiped his eyes with the wet cuff of his tunic, then hung his head in his hands. He could not look her in the eye. <br>
<br>
&quot;Fajera, something happened when I was in Qeynos...&quot;  <p><i>Lover and I went down to the fair, <br>
